text: Bottle from WOB in Destin. Not a big fan of pumpkin beers, but this is at the top of the list. Bourbon flavors prevail with the pumpkin taking an appropriate back seat. Liked better than the higher scoring (but still tasty) Avery Pum(kyn).
Pitch black with a khaki head that fades fast. Nose is pumpkin, heavy spice, vanilla, bourbon and sweet. Sticky palate, heavy pumpkin, alcohol, bourbon, spice, and clove.

Pours cola brown with a thin buff head. Aroma features rum, woody, toasted malt and cloves tones. Flavor offers rum, woody, cloves, toasted malt and subtle molasses notes. Mouthfeel delivers OK body and nice fizz. Roll out the barrel--

UPDATED: JUL 20, 2016 12oz bottle. Dark brown with small tan head. Strong aroma of pumpkin with hints of clove. Tastes of pumpkin, chocolate, bourbon, cinnamon, clove, and malt. Thick mouthfeel. Strong alcohol finish, with a bitter (dissipates as it warms), gingerbread aftertaste.

Burned pumpkin pie aroma. Pours a black color with a tan head. Flavor carries coconut and pumpkin pie spices; a solid stout with a boozy finish.

Notes: Bottle at GABF 15

5/V/16 - bottle @ home - bottled: III/27/15 (2016-512) Thanks to JefVerstraete for sharing the bottle!
Clear dark brown beer, creamy irregular aery beige head, unstable, non adhesive. Aroma: lots and lots of gingerbread, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, very spicy smell. MF: ok carbon, medium body. Taste: veyr spicy, lots of cinnamon, sweet, caramel, more cinnamon. Aftertaste: some chocolate, ginger bread, little sweet. Very nice one! Despite all the spices, its still very balanced!

Bottle at Lakewood. The look is dark, slight tan head, brownish black in color. The smell is chocolate, pumpkin, spiced, nuts, peanut butter, rich, fruit, dough, and good. The taste is the same, good, really big and rich.
Bottle from Kump. Many thanks! Dark brown colour, nose of pumpkin, ginger bread, lots of spices. Sweet and alcoholic. Not bad for a spice beer.
Bottle at tderoeck's place, thanks jef for sharing! Too much spices, pumpkin, meh, not my style.
Pours a dark mahogany brown with small fizzy head. Aromas of nutmeg, fruit, and some bourbon. Flavors of pumpkin, all spice, nutmeg, sour goodness with some bourbon notes.

crank .. . pours a deep brown .. mild head, solid lacing .. soil, pumpkin spice, lots of various chocolate, booze, burn .. . finish is easy and long, a bit sticky .. will age fine .. . . Statistics say that roughly 79% of all accidents happen within the home. Finally, some good news for homeless people.

Pours an opaque dark brown almost black color with khaki colored head. Barrel, whiskey, oak, pumpkin pie spice on the nose; follows onto the palate. Full bodied. Finishes with more barrel character and some pumpkin notes.

Dark brown to black pour with a tan head. The aroma has some pumpkin, cinnamon, whiskey and roasted malt notes. The flavor is huge on the maple with some vanilla, cinnamon, roasted malt and chocolate. Thick mouthfeel and medium carbonation.

Bottle poured into a snifter -- Drank a Pumpkinator prior to cracking open this little jewel. This beer is an experience, the bourbon barrels and the pumpkin spices and characteristics mix so, so well. I wish I had a stash of a million of these bottles so I could enjoy them whenever I wanted. The bottle wasnt quite as good as when I had this on tap at St Arnolds 20th Anniversary party (it blew my mind there), but its still exceptional!
Lots of pumpkin and spice flavors with some alcohol heat. Wood, vanilla and some dark rum flavors swirl.

Black pour. Light tan head. Aroma is bourbon, allspice, pumpkin pie. Taste is light coffee, spices, faint pumpkin pie spice, mellow coffee and chocolate. Smooth palate, thick creamy mouthfeel. Low carbonation nation, really good pumpkin beer.
Bottle. Black pour. Big huge pumpkin and spice nose. Taste is the same with an overload of spice and booze. Way too much going on here.
user_location: Seattle still not near Beersel., Washington, USA

text: (12oz bottle, courtesy of Mora2000) Pours a black body with a medium tan head. Aroma of pumpkin, bourbon, whip cream, vanilla, and raisins. Flavor of pumpkin, cinnamon, allspice, pumpkin spice, molasses, caramel, and chocolate.
Bottle. Pours a clear copper with small beige head that diminishes to nothing. The aroma is stong spice, nutmeg, cinnamon, wood, bourbon. Thin mouth, strong spice, boozy, sweet, very good.

Dark brown pour with a thin tan head. Aroma pumpkin pie spice, syrup, bourbon, and some chocolate. Taste is sweet molasses, pumpkin pie spice, chocolate, a little vanilla and some booze in the finish. Slick palate. Kind of just pumpkinator with more alcohol heat.

Disappointing considering how much I like Pumpkinator and bourbon. Smells incredible, like spiked pumpkin pie. But the alcohol is way to hot and distracting. I bet it will soften up a bit and be great by next year. If only I could stash a bottle away myself -- which continues to be the most frustrating thing about the BB series.
On tap in a water glass, dark brown suede color, lots of pumpkin sweet aroma, bourbony, oak, brown sugar , malty, pumpkin flavors, long sweet bourbon finish

This beer is absolutely fabulous. I found it to have a very oaky and whiskey taste up front. Then you get the pumpkin spice chocolate and fruit over the middle and finishes with the oak and whiskey finish. Must have for any beer Lover!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Bottle...Pour is dark black with a tan fading head.. Nose is pumpkin, chocolate, bourbon, oak, cream, spice..Tatse is nice pumpkin, bourbon, spice, oak, cream, caramel, cinnamon, spice..
